com.unboundid.ldap.sdk

Interface IntermediateResponseListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CollectSupportDataExtendedRequest, DumpDNs, ProxyRequestHandler

    @Extensible
 @ThreadSafety(level=INTERFACE_NOT_THREADSAFE)
public interface IntermediateResponseListener
extends java.io.Serializable
    This interface defines a method that may be used to process intermediate response messages that are returned to the client while processing an operation. If an operation may return intermediate response messages, then an intermediate response listener must be registered with the associated request (via the LDAPRequest.setIntermediateResponseListener(com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.IntermediateResponseListener) method) in order to be able to access the intermediate response messages.
    See Also:
    IntermediateResponse
